<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 06 at 1:52PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Catawba,
northwestern Lincoln and southeastern Burke Counties through 215 PM
EDT...
At 152 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southeast of Morganton, or 7 miles southwest of Icard, moving
east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Hickory, Newton, Conover, Longview, Maiden, Hildebran, Mountain View,
Icard, St. Stephens and Cooksville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
